# Implementation Plan - Fix Scheduler Dispatch Triggers

The CampuGrid pipeline is currently stalling after chunk generation because the system lack "Dispatch Triggers". Chunks are created and queued in Redis, but the Scheduler is never notified to begin the matching process. Additionally, when nodes become available, they don't proactively check the queue.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change involves modifying the core task flow between the AI Pipeline, Redis, and the Scheduler. It will require a restart of both the FastAPI server and the Celery worker to take effect.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Scheduler Logic

#### [MODIFY] [matcher.py](file:///home/samito/Downloads/ECLIPSE/server/app/scheduler/matcher.py)
- Implement `dispatch_next_chunk` task to pop from Redis and trigger a match.
- This ensures that when a node becomes free, it can "pull" work from the queue.

---

### AI Pipeline Completion

#### [MODIFY] [orchestrator.py](file:///home/samito/Downloads/ECLIPSE/server/app/pipeline/orchestrator.py)
- Inject a call to `dispatch_chunk.delay(chunk_id)` immediately after chunk creation.
- This ensures that new jobs are "pushed" to available nodes instantly.

---

### WebSocket Heartbeat Handler

#### [MODIFY] [websocket.py](file:///home/samito/Downloads/ECLIPSE/server/app/api/v1/websocket.py)
- Replace the `TODO` in the heartbeat handler.
- When a node reports as `available: true`, trigger `dispatch_next_chunk.delay()`.

